1
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:48,560
Those dark and glistening eyes

2
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:51,480
And that smiling face of yours

3
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:54,920
No matter what, I can't forget you

4
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:57,960
How your looks have changed

5
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:29,520
Sweetheart

6
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,760
You've grown up

7
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,040
Let Daddy tell you something,

8
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:36,280
no matter what happens,

9
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,320
you've got to learn to look ahead,

10
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,120
okay?

11
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:45,120
But I don't want to look ahead

12
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,280
I just want to look at you

13
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,320
Pops

14
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,360
I miss you

15
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,120
Pops misses you too

16
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,200
Sweetheart

17
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,320
Do you see the brightest star in the sky?

18
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:11,200
That one...

19
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:12,680
that's Pops

20
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,720
Whenever you miss me, just look at it

21
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,480
Pops will always be with you

22
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,240
Really?

23
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,120
Really

24
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,800
Because no matter where you are

25
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,720
I want you to be able

26
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,320
to spot Pops right away

27
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:36,880
But I'll never see you again

28
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,800
Whenever you miss me

29
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,720
Daddy will always be there

30
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,800
Daddy will always be there

31
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:00,320
Don't cry now

32
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,520
Pops

33
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Pops

34
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,800
Where are you?

35
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:21,720
Water!

36
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,400
Why are you so slow?

37
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,320
Are you a snail?

38
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,240
Stop right there!

39
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,240
You can't come in here.

40
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,520
I got in yesterday.

41
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,760
I said no entry, so no entry.

42
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,120
I'm really running out of time.

43
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:40,840
That's final.

44
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:43,080
Your delivery's here.

45
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:45,120
Why not take even longer, huh?

46
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,160
Might as well have it for dinner.

47
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:46,920
Sorry about that.

48
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,160
There was some traffic on the way.

49
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:18,960
Hello?

50
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:19,880
Honey

51
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,880
Xiaohui's competition is tomorrow

52
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,000
Did you get the day off?

53
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,160
Daddy

54
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,400
You have to come

55
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,600
If you don't, you're a puppy!

56
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:28,840
I'll definitely be there

57
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,720
Well,

58
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,280
if you're busy, go take care of it first

59
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,640
Don't overwork yourself, okay?

60
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,840
Xiaohui

61
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:01,240
I'm sorry

62
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:04,200
Daddy has to work overtime

63
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:07,440
I can't make it to your dance competition

64
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:12,120
Okay

65
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:12,840
Daddy

66
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:14,800
Then remember to come home early

67
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,840
Mommy will record a video for you to watch

68
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:21,760
Thank you, doctor

69
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,040
Mr. Wu

70
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:27,440
If you refuse treatment now

71
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,760
your condition will get worse

72
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,480
You need to have surgery immediately

73
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:34,280
Daddy

74
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,120
You haven't seen me dance yet

75
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,560
Today's Saturday

76
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:40,200
Can you please come with me?

77
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,000
Sweetheart

78
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,400
I'm sorry

79
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:45,960
Daddy has to work overtime today

80
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,400
How about this

81
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,440
When I come home tonight

82
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,480
I'll buy you something yummy

83
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:51,920
Okay

84
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:00,840
Daddy

85
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:02,400
Drive safely

86
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,440
Mr. Wu

87
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,560
If you refuse treatment now

88
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,200
your condition will only get worse

89
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,640
You need to have surgery right away

90
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,360
Hello?

91
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:43,680
Hello.

92
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,160
I'd like

93
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,960
to book a funeral

94
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,120
for myself.

95
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:37,600
Are you okay...

96
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:00,440
Oh, right

97
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:03,080
There's a letter in my bedroom drawer

98
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,880
Could you please give it to my wife?

99
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:23,680
Here, take a tissue.

100
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:28,600
Are you okay?

101
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,960
Ever since you got to the Wu house,

102
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,200
you've been acting really strange.

103
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,760
Because I think this world is just too cruel.

104
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,480
Some people preach virtue and morality,

105
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,400
but they're heartless snakes underneath.

106
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,280
Some people try so damn hard,

107
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,200
but misery just won't let them go.

108
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,600
It makes me sick just thinking about it.

109
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,320
I never expected

110
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,120
you to hate evil so passionately.

111
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,240
How refreshingly pure.

112
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:01,720
You don't get it.

113
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,200
If you want to live at peace with this world,

114
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,600
you have to accept its law of the jungle.

115
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:11,080
Accept that society has its hierarchies.

116
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,680
Accept that good people don't always win.

117
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:14,280
And the wicked outlive us all.

118
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:16,080
Otherwise,

119
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,680
you're going to be very disappointed one day.

120
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,040
What about you, Chen Baixi?

121
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:23,400
Have you learned

122
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,400
to live at peace with this world?

123
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,440
Didn't I already tell you?

124
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:29,120
I've already been knocked out of the game.

125
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:30,480
I'm done fighting.

126
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,600
I'm just giving up.

127
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,920
I know why Wu Yuanfeng killed himself.

128
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,280
He had uremia.

129
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,640
Treatment cost a fortune.

130
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,080
And he'd lost his job.

131
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:48,240
He didn't want to burden his family,

132
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:49,600
so he chose to end it all.

133
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:54,000
Actually, I ran into him the night he died.

134
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,320
Right here.

135
00:12:57,680 --> 00:12:58,200
Do you remember?

136
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:00,280
After we split up that day, I came down here.

137
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,880
And I ran right into him.

138
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,600
Back then, I felt something was off about him.

139
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,640
But I didn't think much of it.

140
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,880
I could have stopped him,

141
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:07,680
but I didn't.

142
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,240
You're just like my sister.

143
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,400
Feeling the same guilt.

144
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:13,400
Blaming yourself the same way.

145
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:15,040
But you have to understand,

146
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:15,840
someone dead set on dying,

147
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,960
you can't save them.

148
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,400
Besides,

149
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:23,840
it's not like you can see the future.

150
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:27,080
How do you know I can't?

151
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,560
Come on.

152
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:33,360
Let's get back to work.

153
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:39,760
We found this diagnosis in Mr. Wu's belongings.

154
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:46,880
Uremia.

155
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,800
This...

156
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:50,720
This can't be possible.

157
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:52,840
My husband was always so healthy.

158
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:55,240
Is it possible there's some mistake?

159
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:57,520
Could there be?

160
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,480
Mr. Wu...

161
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,800
He just didn't want you all to worry too much.

162
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,440
That's why he bore it all alone.

163
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:05,520
Mrs. Wu,

164
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:09,160
Mr. Wu specifically asked that this go to you.

165
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,240
Mom

166
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,960
Mrs. Wu

167
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:29,120
My condolences

168
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:11,800
Bow.

169
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:18,440
Begin.

170
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,040
Cleansing the body

171
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,040
Cleansing the ears

172
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:55,960
Grooming the face

173
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,800
Placing hair on the deceased

174
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:22,600
Combing the hair

175
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:28,040
One stroke to comb away worries

176
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,760
Another to comb away old hardships

177
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:36,240
No more ties, no more worries from now on

178
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:39,760
My dear wife

179
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:42,440
By the time you read this letter

180
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:44,680
I'll already be gone

181
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,560
All these years

182
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:50,400
you've given so much to this family

183
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:51,840
Thank you for your hard work

184
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,680
I tried so hard

185
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:59,240
but I couldn't keep my promise to make you happy

186
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,680
I lost my job

187
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:04,720
and then I got uremia

188
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:06,640
I...

189
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:09,080
I didn't dare tell you two

190
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:11,320
afraid it would break your hearts

191
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:15,200
I couldn't bear to see you suffer for my sake

192
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:18,720
I know this illness is a bottomless pit

193
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,720
So

194
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:23,080
I chose to say goodbye to you this way

195
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:25,160
Don't be sad

196
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,640
I believe

197
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:30,520
you'll live on well with Huihui

198
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,720
The money in the bank card

199
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:35,800
is for you to pay off the mortgage

200
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,080
and cover the tuition

201
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:42,480
The password is your birthday

202
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,560
There's also an insurance policy

203
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:49,200
the last bit of security I can give you

204
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:52,840
I wasn't a good husband or father

205
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:01,240
Why... why would you do something so drastic?

206
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,040
But I'm just so tired

207
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:05,000
It hurts so much

208
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:07,920
I said no entry, so no entry

209
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,320
Get the hell out!

210
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:12,560
Wait a second

211
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:14,120
Take off your shoes

212
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:15,600
I called

213
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,280
The line was busy

214
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:17,840
So it's all my fault then?

215
00:18:18,080 --> 00:18:18,880
Right?

216
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:20,200
What are you eating for?

217
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,040
I need results right now

218
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:23,160
Results, you get it?

219
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,200
Lin Wenbin

220
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,720
Are you trying to push me to my death?

221
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,640
Fine then

222
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,760
Right now

223
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,040
I'm finally free

224
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:35,960
I'll be up in heaven

225
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,480
watching over you always

226
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:40,720
I will forever

227
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:41,960
love you both

228
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,600
Don't cry

229
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:50,440
Daddy doesn't like to see you cry like this

230
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:07,560
The marks on the legs need to be treated.

231
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:08,960
You do it.

232
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:13,280
Use the restoration wax.

233
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,680
First treat

234
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,880
the damaged skin.

235
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,720
While restoring,

236
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:22,720
follow the texture of the skin

237
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,760
and apply it slowly.

238
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:32,880
Use foundation

239
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:33,880
to even out the skin tone.

240
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,320
The deceased's skin is a bit yellow,

241
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:38,240
so use number three

242
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,280
with a touch of number two.

243
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:31,400
You

244
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,800
Does it hurt?

245
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,520
Mrs. Wu

246
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:50,840
The departed's body

247
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:51,920
mustn't be touched by tears

248
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:54,840
or he won't be able to let go and leave

249
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:01,880
I'll never see Wu Yuanfeng again

250
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:10,400
I'll never see Wu Yuanfeng again

251
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:22,120
Death is like a blown-out candle

252
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:24,000
They say

253
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:25,960
that when the eternal lamp won't stay lit

254
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:29,160
it means the departed still has lingering ties

255
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:31,280
Stop talking nonsense

256
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:37,360
May the departed rest in peace

257
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:39,400
and reach eternal bliss

258
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:42,360
leaving all worldly ties behind

259
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:45,760
Honey

260
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:46,840
I know

261
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:50,080
you can't stop worrying about me and Xiaohui

262
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,480
Trust me

263
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,640
the two of us will be just fine

264
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:02,480
Once you get to the other side

265
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,480
be good to yourself

266
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,680
Don't skimp on food anymore

267
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:11,160
or on rest

268
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:14,440
Don't make me worry about you

269
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:05,080
Please bow

270
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:07,160
First bow

271
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:12,160
Second bow

272
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:17,600
Third bow

273
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:24,080
Family members may now view the deceased

274
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:50,760
Mom

275
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,160
Life and death are unpredictable

276
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:30,160
Each meets their own fate

277
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:31,600
I'm still not used to it

278
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:36,680
I was just thinking

279
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:41,680
why must our fate always be decided by others?

280
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:43,960
Well, yours isn't

281
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:46,320
You settle every score on the spot

282
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:49,480
Yeah

283
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,280
If someone throws a rock at me

284
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,800
I should at least throw paper back, right?

285
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:57,560
Wu Yuanfeng got laid off

286
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:59,160
and he didn't even get any severance pay

287
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:00,760
We can't just let this slide, right?

288
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,000
Where are you going?

289
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:06,480
Who are you off to see this late at night?

290
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:21,680
These are all the things Old Wu left behind.

291
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:27,120
Back when he was working here,

292
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:28,880
he was grinding away like a spinning top all day.

293
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:29,960
But in the end?

294
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:31,000
He was left with nothing.

295
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:31,680
The company

